text: Area codes 330 and 234 are telephone area code in the North American Numbering Plan (NANP). They serve parts of northeastern Ohio in the United States, such as Akron, Canton, Youngstown, and Wooster. Area code 330 was created on March 9, 1996 as a split from 216. It was overlaid by 234 on October 30, 2000. 330
